Skincare That’s Simple, Affordable, and Effective ✨

Step 1: Cleanse
	•	Start fresh: Rinse with lukewarm water morning and night.
	•	Honey hack: Got honey? Use it as a natural cleanser or mask for its antibacterial magic.
	•	Steam it out: No steamer? No problem. A bowl of hot water + a towel works wonders.

Step 2: Moisturise
	•	Aloe love: Scoop out gel from aloe vera leaves for a natural, soothing moisturiser.
	•	Oil up (sparingly!): Dab a little coconut or olive oil for dry skin relief. Acne-prone? Go easy on this step!

Step 3: Sun Protection
	•	Shade wins: Rock that hat, stay under cover, and layer up to keep UV damage at bay.

Step 4: Healthy Habits
	•	Stay hydrated: Water is your skin’s best friend.
	•	Sleep it off: Beauty sleep is real – your skin repairs while you snooze.
	•	Eat your greens: A diet rich in fruits and veggies equals a glow that lasts.

These tips cost nothing but consistency, and they’ll leave you 1% better every day.

Simple steps. Serious results. 

You’ve got this! 💪

6 Signs Your Skin Needs a Reset:
	1.	Increased Sensitivity: Redness, itchiness, or burning may mean your routine is too harsh. Simplify it to recover.
	2.	Frequent Breakouts: New or frequent breakouts? Your products might not suit your skin.
	3.	Oiliness/Dryness: Sudden texture changes could mean your skin’s balance is off.
	4.	Dullness: Skin looking rough or lackluster? Time for exfoliation and hydration.
	5.	Makeup Issues: Patchy makeup could be due to buildup or lack of hydration.
	6.	Tightness: Persistent tightness means your skin barrier needs support.

🎀 Tip: Simplify to basics—gentle cleanser, moisturiser, and SPF—and consider a facial to reset your skin.
